{
  "video_id": "P_SD5Rt6XMk",
  "method": "api",
  "language": null,
  "duration_seconds": 2.5163652999908663,
  "entry_count": 201,
  "error": null,
  "entries": [
    {
      "time": "00:00",
      "start": 0.06,
      "end": 0.8999999999999999,
      "duration": 0.84,
      "text": "- [Lecturer] What comes to your mind"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:00",
      "start": 0.9,
      "end": 2.7,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "when you hear the word \"radioactive?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "00:02",
      "start": 2.7,
      "end": 6.0,
      "duration": 3.3,
      "text": "Well, for me it was this. Danger, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:06",
      "start": 6.0,
      "end": 7.32,
      "duration": 1.32,
      "text": "But in this video,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:07",
      "start": 7.32,
      "end": 9.96,
      "duration": 2.64,
      "text": "we are trying to understand\nwhat exactly is radioactive"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:09",
      "start": 9.96,
      "end": 13.290000000000001,
      "duration": 3.33,
      "text": "or what does it mean and\nwhy is it so dangerous?"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:13",
      "start": 13.29,
      "end": 16.74,
      "duration": 3.45,
      "text": "And how can the same thing\nbe also useful to us?"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:16",
      "start": 16.74,
      "end": 18.9,
      "duration": 2.16,
      "text": "That's what we'll explore. So let's begin."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:18",
      "start": 18.9,
      "end": 20.49,
      "duration": 1.59,
      "text": "To explore what radioactivity is,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:20",
      "start": 20.49,
      "end": 22.529999999999998,
      "duration": 2.04,
      "text": "let's start with something\nthat you're familiar with."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:22",
      "start": 22.53,
      "end": 25.020000000000003,
      "duration": 2.49,
      "text": "Chemical processes, chemical reactions."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:25",
      "start": 25.02,
      "end": 25.852999999999998,
      "duration": 0.833,
      "text": "Now you don't have to worry"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:25",
      "start": 25.853,
      "end": 27.03,
      "duration": 1.177,
      "text": "about this specific chemical reaction,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:27",
      "start": 27.03,
      "end": 30.03,
      "duration": 3.0,
      "text": "but the thing to focus on is\nin every chemical reaction,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:30",
      "start": 30.03,
      "end": 33.15,
      "duration": 3.12,
      "text": "you find that the number of\nelements on the right-hand side"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:33",
      "start": 33.15,
      "end": 35.489999999999995,
      "duration": 2.34,
      "text": "is exactly the same as the\nnumber of elements on the left."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:35",
      "start": 35.49,
      "end": 38.88,
      "duration": 3.39,
      "text": "For example, you have four\noxygen atoms on the left,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:38",
      "start": 38.88,
      "end": 40.71,
      "duration": 1.83,
      "text": "you find four oxygen atoms on the right."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:40",
      "start": 40.71,
      "end": 42.63,
      "duration": 1.92,
      "text": "You have one carbon atom on the right,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:42",
      "start": 42.63,
      "end": 44.28,
      "duration": 1.65,
      "text": "you have one carbon atom on the left."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:44",
      "start": 44.28,
      "end": 46.17,
      "duration": 1.89,
      "text": "This means that you will never be able"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:46",
      "start": 46.17,
      "end": 48.660000000000004,
      "duration": 2.49,
      "text": "to get new elements in your products."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:48",
      "start": 48.66,
      "end": 50.79,
      "duration": 2.13,
      "text": "The elements on the product\nside will always be the same"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:50",
      "start": 50.79,
      "end": 52.62,
      "duration": 1.83,
      "text": "as the elements on the reactant side."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:52",
      "start": 52.62,
      "end": 55.199999999999996,
      "duration": 2.58,
      "text": "But in contrast, in radioactive processes,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:55",
      "start": 55.2,
      "end": 57.57,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "you get new elements."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:57",
      "start": 57.57,
      "end": 59.67,
      "duration": 2.1,
      "text": "What? How?"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:59",
      "start": 59.67,
      "end": 61.440000000000005,
      "duration": 1.77,
      "text": "You see, in chemical reactions,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:01",
      "start": 61.44,
      "end": 62.76,
      "duration": 1.32,
      "text": "the reason you don't get new elements"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:02",
      "start": 62.76,
      "end": 64.59,
      "duration": 1.83,
      "text": "is because it's all about electrons"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:04",
      "start": 64.59,
      "end": 66.15,
      "duration": 1.56,
      "text": "going from one atom to another."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:06",
      "start": 66.15,
      "end": 67.86,
      "duration": 1.71,
      "text": "And now if you take\nsomething like, say, carbon,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:07",
      "start": 67.86,
      "end": 70.92,
      "duration": 3.06,
      "text": "and you remove electrons from\nit or you add electron to it,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:10",
      "start": 70.92,
      "end": 73.11,
      "duration": 2.19,
      "text": "or you share electrons, whatever you do,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:13",
      "start": 73.11,
      "end": 74.64,
      "duration": 1.53,
      "text": "carbon stays carbon."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:14",
      "start": 74.64,
      "end": 78.12,
      "duration": 3.48,
      "text": "Electrons do not define\nthe identity of an element."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:18",
      "start": 78.12,
      "end": 80.7,
      "duration": 2.58,
      "text": "So now that brings us to\nthe question then what does?"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:20",
      "start": 80.7,
      "end": 84.48,
      "duration": 3.78,
      "text": "What makes carbon carbon?\nWhat makes oxygen oxygen?"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:24",
      "start": 84.48,
      "end": 87.0,
      "duration": 2.52,
      "text": "Well, to answer that question,\nwe need to dig deeper."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:27",
      "start": 87.0,
      "end": 88.74,
      "duration": 1.74,
      "text": "I mean, literally."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:28",
      "start": 88.74,
      "end": 91.67999999999999,
      "duration": 2.94,
      "text": "If you were to look\ninside, say, a carbon atom,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:31",
      "start": 91.68,
      "end": 93.84,
      "duration": 2.16,
      "text": "you'll probably find\nelectrons zooming around."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:33",
      "start": 93.84,
      "end": 96.21000000000001,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "But if you zoom in to the center,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:36",
      "start": 96.21,
      "end": 99.11999999999999,
      "duration": 2.91,
      "text": "you would get the nucleus of the carbon."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:39",
      "start": 99.12,
      "end": 101.55000000000001,
      "duration": 2.43,
      "text": "And you probably already\nknow the nucleus of an atom"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:41",
      "start": 101.55,
      "end": 104.88,
      "duration": 3.33,
      "text": "contains protons, which are\npositively charged particles,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:44",
      "start": 104.88,
      "end": 107.78999999999999,
      "duration": 2.91,
      "text": "and neutrons, which are neutral particles."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:47",
      "start": 107.79,
      "end": 108.81,
      "duration": 1.02,
      "text": "Now guess what?"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:48",
      "start": 108.81,
      "end": 111.12,
      "duration": 2.31,
      "text": "Turns out the identity of an element"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:51",
      "start": 111.12,
      "end": 113.73,
      "duration": 2.61,
      "text": "is defined by the number of protons."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:53",
      "start": 113.73,
      "end": 118.5,
      "duration": 4.77,
      "text": "So for example, anything that\nhas six protons is carbon."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:58",
      "start": 118.5,
      "end": 122.07,
      "duration": 3.57,
      "text": "Carbon is carbon because\nit has six protons."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:02",
      "start": 122.07,
      "end": 126.08999999999999,
      "duration": 4.02,
      "text": "Similarly, anything that has\nseven protons will be nitrogen,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:06",
      "start": 126.09,
      "end": 127.38000000000001,
      "duration": 1.29,
      "text": "and so on and so forth."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:07",
      "start": 127.38,
      "end": 131.01,
      "duration": 3.63,
      "text": "It's the number of protons\nthat decide the identity."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:11",
      "start": 131.01,
      "end": 133.70999999999998,
      "duration": 2.7,
      "text": "But you may ask, \"Well, what\nabout the number of neutrons?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "02:13",
      "start": 133.71,
      "end": 136.95000000000002,
      "duration": 3.24,
      "text": "Ah, the number of neutrons\ndon't matter actually."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:16",
      "start": 136.95,
      "end": 141.78,
      "duration": 4.83,
      "text": "So for example, you can have\ncarbon which has six neutrons,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:21",
      "start": 141.78,
      "end": 144.78,
      "duration": 3.0,
      "text": "or you can have carbon\nwhich has eight neutrons."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:24",
      "start": 144.78,
      "end": 147.09,
      "duration": 2.31,
      "text": "You have different nuclei\nof carbon available."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:27",
      "start": 147.09,
      "end": 149.13,
      "duration": 2.04,
      "text": "And by the way, such nuclei,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:29",
      "start": 149.13,
      "end": 152.25,
      "duration": 3.12,
      "text": "which have the same number of protons,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:32",
      "start": 152.25,
      "end": 153.45,
      "duration": 1.2,
      "text": "which mean the same element,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:33",
      "start": 153.45,
      "end": 157.17,
      "duration": 3.72,
      "text": "but different number of\nneutrons, we give them a name,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:37",
      "start": 157.17,
      "end": 159.42,
      "duration": 2.25,
      "text": "We call them isotopes."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:39",
      "start": 159.42,
      "end": 161.73,
      "duration": 2.31,
      "text": "And so in order to be able\nto differentiate them,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:41",
      "start": 161.73,
      "end": 162.92999999999998,
      "duration": 1.2,
      "text": "we have a notation."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:42",
      "start": 162.93,
      "end": 165.33,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "So the notation we use\nfor representing nuclei"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:45",
      "start": 165.33,
      "end": 166.65,
      "duration": 1.32,
      "text": "is we write the C,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:46",
      "start": 166.65,
      "end": 170.07,
      "duration": 3.42,
      "text": "and then we write the number\nof protons over here down,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:50",
      "start": 170.07,
      "end": 171.75,
      "duration": 1.68,
      "text": "and then on the top left,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:51",
      "start": 171.75,
      "end": 174.09,
      "duration": 2.34,
      "text": "we write the total number of particles,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:54",
      "start": 174.09,
      "end": 174.99,
      "duration": 0.9,
      "text": "not the number of neutrons."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:54",
      "start": 174.99,
      "end": 177.72,
      "duration": 2.73,
      "text": "So it's six plus six, 12."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:57",
      "start": 177.72,
      "end": 182.22,
      "duration": 4.5,
      "text": "So this is how we represent\nthis nuclei. Nucleus, sorry."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:02",
      "start": 182.22,
      "end": 184.17,
      "duration": 1.95,
      "text": "Similarly, how would you\nrepresent this nucleus?"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:04",
      "start": 184.17,
      "end": 187.64999999999998,
      "duration": 3.48,
      "text": "Well, we'll represent as\nC six. It has to be six."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:07",
      "start": 187.65,
      "end": 189.36,
      "duration": 1.71,
      "text": "If it wasn't six, it wouldn't be carbon."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:09",
      "start": 189.36,
      "end": 192.60000000000002,
      "duration": 3.24,
      "text": "And then on the top left, you\nwould write six plus eight."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:12",
      "start": 192.6,
      "end": 195.12,
      "duration": 2.52,
      "text": "We would represent this as 14."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:15",
      "start": 195.12,
      "end": 198.9,
      "duration": 3.78,
      "text": "So we would call this\nthe carbon-12 isotope,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:18",
      "start": 198.9,
      "end": 202.47,
      "duration": 3.57,
      "text": "and we would call this\nthe carbon-14 isotope."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:22",
      "start": 202.47,
      "end": 204.6,
      "duration": 2.13,
      "text": "And so you can see it's this number,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:24",
      "start": 204.6,
      "end": 205.85999999999999,
      "duration": 1.26,
      "text": "the total number of particles,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:25",
      "start": 205.86,
      "end": 207.93,
      "duration": 2.07,
      "text": "that differentiate the isotopes."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:27",
      "start": 207.93,
      "end": 209.1,
      "duration": 1.17,
      "text": "We give a name to that number."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:29",
      "start": 209.1,
      "end": 210.46,
      "duration": 1.36,
      "text": "We call it the mass number"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:31",
      "start": 211.41,
      "end": 214.35,
      "duration": 2.94,
      "text": "because that number represents\nthe mass in the sense,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:34",
      "start": 214.35,
      "end": 216.69,
      "duration": 2.34,
      "text": "you know, here you have 14 particles"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:36",
      "start": 216.69,
      "end": 218.64,
      "duration": 1.95,
      "text": "so this nucleus will have more mass"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:38",
      "start": 218.64,
      "end": 220.2,
      "duration": 1.56,
      "text": "compared to this nucleus,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:40",
      "start": 220.2,
      "end": 222.20999999999998,
      "duration": 2.01,
      "text": "which has only 12 particles, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:42",
      "start": 222.21,
      "end": 223.65,
      "duration": 1.44,
      "text": "And so when it comes to nuclei,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:43",
      "start": 223.65,
      "end": 224.94,
      "duration": 1.29,
      "text": "the mass number matters"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:44",
      "start": 224.94,
      "end": 227.43,
      "duration": 2.49,
      "text": "because you care about\nboth protons and neutrons."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:47",
      "start": 227.43,
      "end": 229.41,
      "duration": 1.98,
      "text": "But when it comes to chemical reactions,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:49",
      "start": 229.41,
      "end": 230.91,
      "duration": 1.5,
      "text": "you don't care about\nthe number of neutrons,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:50",
      "start": 230.91,
      "end": 232.38,
      "duration": 1.47,
      "text": "you only talk about carbon"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:52",
      "start": 232.38,
      "end": 234.72,
      "duration": 2.34,
      "text": "because they both have the\nsame chemical properties,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:54",
      "start": 234.72,
      "end": 237.66,
      "duration": 2.94,
      "text": "but not the same nuclear properties."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:57",
      "start": 237.66,
      "end": 239.28,
      "duration": 1.62,
      "text": "Now you might say, \"Mahesh,\nall of this is great,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:59",
      "start": 239.28,
      "end": 241.41,
      "duration": 2.13,
      "text": "but what exactly is radioactivity"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:01",
      "start": 241.41,
      "end": 243.06,
      "duration": 1.65,
      "text": "and how does it create new elements?"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:03",
      "start": 243.06,
      "end": 244.5,
      "duration": 1.44,
      "text": "And why is it so dangerous?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "04:04",
      "start": 244.5,
      "end": 247.05,
      "duration": 2.55,
      "text": "Well, in short, turns\nout that certain nuclei"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:07",
      "start": 247.05,
      "end": 248.43,
      "duration": 1.38,
      "text": "can be very unstable,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:08",
      "start": 248.43,
      "end": 250.8,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "and for such cases, for such nuclei,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:10",
      "start": 250.8,
      "end": 253.83,
      "duration": 3.03,
      "text": "they just automatically,\njust spontaneously,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:13",
      "start": 253.83,
      "end": 255.51000000000002,
      "duration": 1.68,
      "text": "spit out some particles."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:15",
      "start": 255.51,
      "end": 259.62,
      "duration": 4.11,
      "text": "And in doing so, the number\nof protons in them changes."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:19",
      "start": 259.62,
      "end": 261.81,
      "duration": 2.19,
      "text": "As a result, the element changes,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:21",
      "start": 261.81,
      "end": 263.88,
      "duration": 2.07,
      "text": "and that's how you get new elements."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:23",
      "start": 263.88,
      "end": 267.27,
      "duration": 3.39,
      "text": "That process is what\nwe call radioactivity."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:27",
      "start": 267.27,
      "end": 270.09,
      "duration": 2.82,
      "text": "Now, I know there's a lot to\nunpack and we'll do this now."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:30",
      "start": 270.09,
      "end": 271.56699999999995,
      "duration": 1.477,
      "text": "So the first question you might have is"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:31",
      "start": 271.567,
      "end": 273.783,
      "duration": 2.216,
      "text": "\"What do you mean by\nnucleus being unstable?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "04:33",
      "start": 273.783,
      "end": 275.97,
      "duration": 2.187,
      "text": "Now, it's not really straightforward"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:35",
      "start": 275.97,
      "end": 278.31,
      "duration": 2.34,
      "text": "to understand the stability of a nucleus."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:38",
      "start": 278.31,
      "end": 282.66,
      "duration": 4.35,
      "text": "But to gain some intuition,\nthink about very heavy nuclei."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:42",
      "start": 282.66,
      "end": 284.97,
      "duration": 2.31,
      "text": "If you have a very heavy\nnucleus, you can kind of think,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:44",
      "start": 284.97,
      "end": 286.65000000000003,
      "duration": 1.68,
      "text": "understand that it has a lot of protons,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:46",
      "start": 286.65,
      "end": 288.87,
      "duration": 2.22,
      "text": "and all the protons want\nto go away from each other"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:48",
      "start": 288.87,
      "end": 290.61,
      "duration": 1.74,
      "text": "because they have all positive charges,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:50",
      "start": 290.61,
      "end": 293.28000000000003,
      "duration": 2.67,
      "text": "that makes it so hard to\nkeep the nucleus together."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:53",
      "start": 293.28,
      "end": 295.91999999999996,
      "duration": 2.64,
      "text": "So you can kind of see\nthat very heavy nuclei"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:55",
      "start": 295.92,
      "end": 297.42,
      "duration": 1.5,
      "text": "tend to be unstable."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:57",
      "start": 297.42,
      "end": 299.61,
      "duration": 2.19,
      "text": "But what is not so intuitive"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:59",
      "start": 299.61,
      "end": 302.34000000000003,
      "duration": 2.73,
      "text": "is that light nuclei can also be unstable."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:02",
      "start": 302.34,
      "end": 306.06,
      "duration": 3.72,
      "text": "For example, C-14 is an unstable nucleus"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:06",
      "start": 306.06,
      "end": 308.64,
      "duration": 2.58,
      "text": "versus C-12 is stable."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:08",
      "start": 308.64,
      "end": 310.5,
      "duration": 1.86,
      "text": "Now, you may be wondering,\n\"Well, how can that be?"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:10",
      "start": 310.5,
      "end": 312.72,
      "duration": 2.22,
      "text": "They both have the same\nnumber of protons.\""
    },
    {
      "time": "05:12",
      "start": 312.72,
      "end": 317.64000000000004,
      "duration": 4.92,
      "text": "Well, turns out that stability\nalso depends upon the ratio"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:17",
      "start": 317.64,
      "end": 320.34,
      "duration": 2.7,
      "text": "of the number of protons\nand the number of neutrons."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:20",
      "start": 320.34,
      "end": 322.89,
      "duration": 2.55,
      "text": "Certain ratios are more\nstable compared to the others."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:22",
      "start": 322.89,
      "end": 324.99,
      "duration": 2.1,
      "text": "And like I said, it's\nnot very straightforward,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:24",
      "start": 324.99,
      "end": 326.49,
      "duration": 1.5,
      "text": "it's not very intuitive."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:26",
      "start": 326.49,
      "end": 327.87,
      "duration": 1.38,
      "text": "And so we'll not have to remember"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:27",
      "start": 327.87,
      "end": 329.88,
      "duration": 2.01,
      "text": "which nuclei is stable\nor which nuclei are not."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:29",
      "start": 329.88,
      "end": 331.68,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "But the bottom line is there are certain"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:31",
      "start": 331.68,
      "end": 333.27,
      "duration": 1.59,
      "text": "nuclei that are unstable."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:33",
      "start": 333.27,
      "end": 335.34,
      "duration": 2.07,
      "text": "They can be heavy or they can be light."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:35",
      "start": 335.34,
      "end": 337.79999999999995,
      "duration": 2.46,
      "text": "Now let's see what happens\nto these unstable nuclei."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:37",
      "start": 337.8,
      "end": 339.78000000000003,
      "duration": 1.98,
      "text": "So let's take an example."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:39",
      "start": 339.78,
      "end": 342.41999999999996,
      "duration": 2.64,
      "text": "If you take carbon-14, turns out that,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:42",
      "start": 342.42,
      "end": 343.38,
      "duration": 0.96,
      "text": "because it's unstable,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:43",
      "start": 343.38,
      "end": 346.46999999999997,
      "duration": 3.09,
      "text": "it spits out something\ncalled the beta particle,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:46",
      "start": 346.47,
      "end": 350.70000000000005,
      "duration": 4.23,
      "text": "and, in the result,\nchanges to nitrogen-14."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:50",
      "start": 350.7,
      "end": 352.657,
      "duration": 1.957,
      "text": "Now, I know you might be\nhaving a lot of questions like,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:52",
      "start": 352.657,
      "end": 355.65,
      "duration": 2.993,
      "text": "\"How does that happen? What\nexactly is a beta particle?"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:55",
      "start": 355.65,
      "end": 357.75,
      "duration": 2.1,
      "text": "And how did the number of protons increase"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:57",
      "start": 357.75,
      "end": 358.583,
      "duration": 0.833,
      "text": "from six to seven?"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:58",
      "start": 358.583,
      "end": 359.58000000000004,
      "duration": 0.997,
      "text": "How did that happen?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "05:59",
      "start": 359.58,
      "end": 361.62,
      "duration": 2.04,
      "text": "We'll get into all of\nthis in the future videos."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:01",
      "start": 361.62,
      "end": 363.87,
      "duration": 2.25,
      "text": "In fact, this is called the beta decay."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:03",
      "start": 363.87,
      "end": 366.42,
      "duration": 2.55,
      "text": "There's something called\nalpha decay and gamma decay."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:06",
      "start": 366.42,
      "end": 368.79,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "But we'll get into all\nthe fun stuff later on."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:08",
      "start": 368.79,
      "end": 371.52000000000004,
      "duration": 2.73,
      "text": "But the point to see over\nhere is look at what happened."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:11",
      "start": 371.52,
      "end": 375.12,
      "duration": 3.6,
      "text": "We started with an\nunstable parent nucleus,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:15",
      "start": 375.12,
      "end": 376.56,
      "duration": 1.44,
      "text": "that's what we call\nthem, the parent nucleus,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:16",
      "start": 376.56,
      "end": 377.88,
      "duration": 1.32,
      "text": "which is unstable."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:17",
      "start": 377.88,
      "end": 379.59,
      "duration": 1.71,
      "text": "It's spontaneously,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:19",
      "start": 379.59,
      "end": 381.96,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "meaning without us having\nto do anything to it,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:21",
      "start": 381.96,
      "end": 384.21,
      "duration": 2.25,
      "text": "it just happened all by\nitself because it's unstable,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:24",
      "start": 384.21,
      "end": 388.22999999999996,
      "duration": 4.02,
      "text": "spontaneously changed into\na more stable nucleus,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:28",
      "start": 388.23,
      "end": 390.72,
      "duration": 2.49,
      "text": "which we call the daughter nucleus, okay?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:30",
      "start": 390.72,
      "end": 393.21000000000004,
      "duration": 2.49,
      "text": "And in doing so, what has it done?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:33",
      "start": 393.21,
      "end": 397.16999999999996,
      "duration": 3.96,
      "text": "It has spit out some high energy particle."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:37",
      "start": 397.17,
      "end": 398.73,
      "duration": 1.56,
      "text": "In fact, that's how you\nbecome stable, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:38",
      "start": 398.73,
      "end": 400.14000000000004,
      "duration": 1.41,
      "text": "Like you let go of some,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:40",
      "start": 400.14,
      "end": 402.33,
      "duration": 2.19,
      "text": "you release some energy, and guess what?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:42",
      "start": 402.33,
      "end": 405.0,
      "duration": 2.67,
      "text": "It's this high energy particle,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:45",
      "start": 405.0,
      "end": 407.55,
      "duration": 2.55,
      "text": "that's what makes\nradioactivity so dangerous."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:47",
      "start": 407.55,
      "end": 408.38300000000004,
      "duration": 0.833,
      "text": "Now, you might say,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:48",
      "start": 408.383,
      "end": 410.15999999999997,
      "duration": 1.777,
      "text": "\"Mahesh, what do you mean by high energy?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:50",
      "start": 410.16,
      "end": 412.53000000000003,
      "duration": 2.37,
      "text": "Like a moving ping pong ball"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:52",
      "start": 412.53,
      "end": 415.95,
      "duration": 3.42,
      "text": "would literally have billions\nof more Joules energy, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:55",
      "start": 415.95,
      "end": 417.42,
      "duration": 1.47,
      "text": "So what do you mean by energy?\""
    },
    {
      "time": "06:57",
      "start": 417.42,
      "end": 419.7,
      "duration": 2.28,
      "text": "Well, you're right, but\nunlike a ping pong ball,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:59",
      "start": 419.7,
      "end": 423.59999999999997,
      "duration": 3.9,
      "text": "these particles can actually\nenter into your cells' atoms"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:03",
      "start": 423.6,
      "end": 425.13,
      "duration": 1.53,
      "text": "and knock off electrons,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:05",
      "start": 425.13,
      "end": 428.58,
      "duration": 3.45,
      "text": "destroying bonds, which\ncould damage the cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:08",
      "start": 428.58,
      "end": 430.71,
      "duration": 2.13,
      "text": "which could mutate your DNA.\""
    },
    {
      "time": "07:10",
      "start": 430.71,
      "end": 433.68,
      "duration": 2.97,
      "text": "That's what makes them so dangerous."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:13",
      "start": 433.68,
      "end": 435.93,
      "duration": 2.25,
      "text": "So when I say high energy particles,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:15",
      "start": 435.93,
      "end": 439.38,
      "duration": 3.45,
      "text": "what we mean over here is\nthese are ionizing particles."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:19",
      "start": 439.38,
      "end": 440.82,
      "duration": 1.44,
      "text": "We call them ionizing radiation."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:20",
      "start": 440.82,
      "end": 445.11,
      "duration": 4.29,
      "text": "Ionizing means they have the\nability to knock off electrons."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:25",
      "start": 445.11,
      "end": 448.8,
      "duration": 3.69,
      "text": "But here's the thing, the same\nthing can be useful for us."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:28",
      "start": 448.8,
      "end": 451.56,
      "duration": 2.76,
      "text": "For example, we can target\nthese at cancer cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:31",
      "start": 451.56,
      "end": 452.91,
      "duration": 1.35,
      "text": "and try and destroy them."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:32",
      "start": 452.91,
      "end": 455.61,
      "duration": 2.7,
      "text": "That's what radiation\ntherapy is all about."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:35",
      "start": 455.61,
      "end": 458.79,
      "duration": 3.18,
      "text": "So if you understand\nradioactivity, we can control it"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:38",
      "start": 458.79,
      "end": 462.24,
      "duration": 3.45,
      "text": "and we can use it for\nsome amazing applications."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:42",
      "start": 462.24,
      "end": 463.83,
      "duration": 1.59,
      "text": "Anyways, that's it for this video."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:43",
      "start": 463.83,
      "end": 465.71999999999997,
      "duration": 1.89,
      "text": "So in short, what is radioactivity"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:45",
      "start": 465.72,
      "end": 467.64000000000004,
      "duration": 1.92,
      "text": "or what is radioactive decay?"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:47",
      "start": 467.64,
      "end": 471.24,
      "duration": 3.6,
      "text": "It's a process in which you\nhave an unstable nucleus"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:51",
      "start": 471.24,
      "end": 476.01,
      "duration": 4.77,
      "text": "that spontaneously changes\nto a new, more stable nucleus"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:56",
      "start": 476.01,
      "end": 476.88,
      "duration": 0.87,
      "text": "and, in doing so,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:56",
      "start": 476.88,
      "end": 480.573,
      "duration": 3.693,
      "text": "it releases high energy,\nionizing radiation."
    }
  ]
}